data19 <- GlobalTemperatures$LandAverageTemperature[1801:3192]
data20 <- GlobalTemperatures$LandAverageTemperature[3001:3192]
ts19 <- ts(data19, start = c(1900,1), frequency = 12)
ts20 <- ts(data20, start = c(2000,1), frequency = 12)
train_split <- window(ts20, start = c(2000,1), end = c(2012,12))
test_split <- window(ts20, start = c(2013,1), end = c(2015,12))

From the graph above, we can see that by doing diff(diff(train_split, ,lag = 12), we did deseasonalize the time series and get stationary data, both proved by acf graph(no obvious seasonality) and kpss.test(p-value > 0.05, cannot reject the null hypothesis).

train_split <- window(ts20, start = c(2000,1), end = c(2012,12))

Simple Regression Sliding & Expanding Window

k <- 156
n <- length(ts19)
p <- 12
H <- 36
st <- tsp(ts19)[1]+(k-2)/p #  gives the start time in time units,

e_1 <- matrix(NA,n-k-35,H)
e_2 <- matrix(NA,n-k-35,H)
  
for(i in 1:(n-k-35)){
  
  
  time_slid <-1:156
  time_exp <- 1:(156+(i-1))
  

  ### One Month rolling forecasting
  # Expanding Window 
  train_1 <- window(ts19, end= st + i/p)  ## Window Length: k+i
  
  # Sliding Window - keep the training window of fixed length. 
  # The training set always consists of k observations.
  train_2 <- window(ts19, start=st+(i-k+1)/p, end=st+i/p) ## Window Length: k
  
  test <- window(ts19, start=st + (i+1)/p, end=st + (i+H)/p) ## Window Length: H

  if (i > 1199) {
  cat(c("*** CV", i,":","len(Expanding Window):",length(train_1), "len(Sliding Window):",length(train_2), "len(Test):",length(test),'\n'  ))
  cat(c("*** TRAIN -  Expanding WIndow:",tsp(train_1)[1],'-',tsp(train_1)[2],'\n'))
  cat(c("*** TRAIN - Sliding WIndow:",tsp(train_2)[1],'-',tsp(train_2)[2],'\n'))
  cat(c("*** TEST:",tsp(test)[1],'-',tsp(test)[2],'\n'))
  cat("*************************** \n \n")
  }

  sr_exp <- lm(train_1 ~ time_exp)
  sr_exp_forecast <- forecast(sr_exp, newdata = time(test))
  
  sr_slid <- lm(train_2 ~ time_slid)
  sr_slid_forecast <- forecast(sr_slid, newdata = time(test))
  
  e_1[i,1:length(test)] <- sr_exp_forecast$mean - test
  e_2[i,1:length(test)] <- sr_slid_forecast$mean - test
}
## *** CV 1200 : len(Expanding Window): 1355 len(Sliding Window): 156 len(Test): 36 
## *** TRAIN -  Expanding WIndow: 1900 - 2012.83333333333 
## *** TRAIN - Sliding WIndow: 1999.91666666667 - 2012.83333333333 
## *** TEST: 2012.91666666667 - 2015.83333333333 
## *************************** 
##  
## *** CV 1201 : len(Expanding Window): 1356 len(Sliding Window): 156 len(Test): 36 
## *** TRAIN -  Expanding WIndow: 1900 - 2012.91666666667 
## *** TRAIN - Sliding WIndow: 2000 - 2012.91666666667 
## *** TEST: 2013 - 2015.91666666667 
## *************************** 
## 
mae_slid_lr <- abs(e_2)
lr_slid_mae <- mean(mae_slid_lr[(n-k-35),], na.rm = T)

mae_exp_lr <- abs(e_1)
lr_exp_mae <- mean(mae_exp_lr[(n-k-35)], na.rm = T)

rmse_exp_lr <- (e_1)^2
lr_exp_rmse <- sqrt(mean(rmse_exp_lr[(n-k-35),], na.rm = T))

rmse_slid_lr <- (e_2)^2
lr_slid_rmse <- sqrt(mean(rmse_slid_lr[(n-k-35),], na.rm = T))

cbind(lr_slid_mae, lr_exp_mae, lr_slid_rmse, lr_exp_rmse)
##      lr_slid_mae lr_exp_mae lr_slid_rmse lr_exp_rmse
## [1,]    6.091575   6.227359     7.340063    4.102538
plot(1:36, colMeans(abs(e_1)), type="l",col=1,xlab="horizon", ylab="MAE", ylim = c(3, 14), main = 'MAE')
lines(1:36, colMeans(abs(e_2)), type="l",col=2)
legend("topleft",legend=c("Simple regression - Expanding Window","Simple regression - Sliding Window"),col=1:2,lty=1)

plot(1:36, sqrt(colMeans((e_1)^2,na.rm=TRUE)), type="l",col=1,xlab="horizon", ylab="RMSE", ylim = c(3.5, 15), 
     main = 'RMSE')
lines(1:36, sqrt(colMeans((e_2)^2,na.rm=TRUE)), type="l",col=2)
legend("topleft",legend=c("Simple regression - Expanding Window","Simple regression - Sliding Window"),col=1:2,lty=1)

tslm <- tslm(train_split ~ trend + season)
tslmfcst <- forecast(tslm, h = 36)

mae_tslm <- mae(test_split, as.numeric(tslmfcst$mean))

TSLM Sliding & Expanding Window

e2_1 <- matrix(NA,n-k-35,H)
e2_2 <- matrix(NA,n-k-35,H)
  
for(i in 1:(n-k-35)){
  

  ### One Month rolling forecasting
  # Expanding Window 
  train_1 <- window(ts19, end= st + i/p)  ## Window Length: k+i
  
  # Sliding Window - keep the training window of fixed length. 
  # The training set always consists of k observations.
  train_2 <- window(ts19, start=st+(i-k+1)/p, end=st+i/p) ## Window Length: k
  
  test <- window(ts19, start=st + (i+1)/p, end=st + (i+H)/p) ## Window Length: H

  tslm_exp <- tslm(train_1 ~ trend + season)
  tslm_exp_forecast <- forecast(tslm_exp, newdata = time(test))

  
  tslm_slid <- tslm(train_2 ~ trend + season)
  tslm_slid_forecast <- forecast(tslm_slid, newdata = time(test))
  
  e2_1[i,1:length(test)] <- as.numeric(tslm_exp_forecast$mean) - test
  e2_2[i,1:length(test)] <- as.numeric(tslm_slid_forecast$mean) - test
  
}
mae_slid_summary <- abs(e2_2)
tslm_slid_mae <- mean(mae_slid_summary[(n-k-35),])

mae_exp_summary <- abs(e2_1)
tslm_exp_mae <- mean(mae_exp_summary[(n-k-35),])

rmse_slid_summary <- (e2_2)^2
tslm_slid_rmse <- sqrt(mean(rmse_slid_summary[(n-k-35),]))

rmse_exp_summary <- (e2_1)^2
tslm_exp_rmse <- sqrt(mean(rmse_exp_summary[(n-k-35),]))

cbind(tslm_slid_mae, tslm_exp_mae, tslm_slid_rmse, tslm_exp_rmse)
##      tslm_slid_mae tslm_exp_mae tslm_slid_rmse tslm_exp_rmse
## [1,]     0.2081363    0.3758574      0.2901131     0.4413595

plot(1:36, colMeans(abs(e2_1), na.rm = T), type=l,col=3,xlab=horizon, ylab=MAE, ylim = c(4.5, 5.5), main = MAE) lines(1:36, colMeans(abs(e2_2)), type=l,col=4) legend(topleft,legend=c(tslm - Expanding Window,tslm - Sliding Window),col=3:4,lty=1)

plot(1:36, colMeans(abs(e2_1),na.rm=TRUE), type="l",col=3,xlab="horizon", ylab="MAE", ylim = c(0.23, 0.32), 
     main = 'MAE')
lines(1:36, colMeans(abs(e2_2),na.rm=TRUE), type="l",col=4)
legend("topleft",legend=c("tslm - Expanding Window","tslm - Sliding Window"),col=3:4,lty=1)

plot(1:36, sqrt(colMeans((e2_1)^2,na.rm=TRUE)), type="l",col=3,xlab="horizon", ylab="RMSE", ylim = c(0.3, .4), 
     main = 'RMSE')
lines(1:36, sqrt(colMeans((e2_2)^2,na.rm=TRUE)), type="l",col=4)
legend("topleft",legend=c("tslm - Expanding Window","tslm - Sliding Window"),col=3:4,lty=1)
